{"questionId":"29618844","questionHtml":"<p>Using mathematical induction and the definition&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mi>r</mi><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>!</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>, prove that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>r</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp;for all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Base case <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>: LHS&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mrow><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>1</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp;and RHS <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mrow><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts></math>, so true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R0</strong></em> if the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>1</mn></mmultiscripts></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>2</mn></mmultiscripts></math> are not evaluated.</p>\n<p>Subsequent marks can still be awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>assume true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> ie <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>k</mi></munderover><mmultiscripts><mrow><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>r</mi></mmultiscripts></math> for some <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The assumption of truth must be clear.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>M0</strong></em> for statements such as “let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>” or “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> is true”.</p>\n<p>Subsequent marks can still be awarded.</p>\n<p>consider <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>LHS<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munderover><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>r</mi></mmultiscripts></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>k</mi></munderover><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mi>r</mi></mmultiscripts><mo>+</mo><mmultiscripts><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mrow><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mo>+</mo><mmultiscripts><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn><mrow></mrow></msubsup><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to cancel factorials and use a common denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use a common denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>!</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>!</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn><mrow></mrow><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mmultiscripts></math></p>\n<p>since true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, and true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;implies true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,</p>\n<p>therefore true for all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award the final <em><strong>R1</strong></em> if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> of the previous <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> marks have been awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Throughout this question, condone presence of any additional terms once the first two correct terms are seen.</p>","meta":{"questionId":"29618844","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.7","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Using mathematical induction and the definition Crn=n!r!n-r!, prove that Σr=1nC1r=C2n+1 for all n∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.10—Perms and combs, binomial with negative and fractional indices","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}